{{Main article|2025 Bangsamoro Parliament election|}}
There are 80 seats in the Bangsamoro Parliament, which be contested for the first time within this election after the inaugural election for the legislature was postponed to 2025. Of the 80 seats, 40 are elected through proportional representation, 32 are elected by single-member districts, and eight are reserved for sectoral representatives. However, the 7 seats allocated for Sulu would not be included, as the Supreme Court of the Philippines|Supreme Court ruled its exclusion from the Bangsamoro in 2024. On the eight sectoral representatives, only four shall be elected on this day, with the other four being decided upon in conventions.
